00:02:46.640 --> 00:02:51.200
[Amit Varma]: All around us we hear about unicorns, and many of these unicorns create notional value

00:02:51.200 --> 00:02:53.000
[Amit Varma]: in the world of bits and bytes.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:58.200
[Amit Varma]: But the sponsor of today's episode is a giant company that creates real value in the world

00:02:58.200 --> 00:02:59.200
[Amit Varma]: of atoms.

00:02:59.200 --> 00:03:04.940
[Amit Varma]: KNST is an aluminium formwork company that was founded in 2014 and is today India's largest

00:03:04.940 --> 00:03:07.240
[Amit Varma]: and the world's largest growing formwork company.

00:03:07.240 --> 00:03:08.680
[Amit Varma]: Now, what is formwork?

00:03:08.680 --> 00:03:13.920
[Amit Varma]: It's a building technology that makes construction more efficient, sustainable, and scalable.

00:03:13.920 --> 00:03:18.800
[Amit Varma]: Until recently, Indian real estate had to outsource this tech to foreign companies at

00:03:18.800 --> 00:03:20.080
[Amit Varma]: crazy prices.

00:03:20.080 --> 00:03:24.800
[Amit Varma]: KNST changed the game with their state-of-the-art automated unit and the largest design team

00:03:24.800 --> 00:03:29.880
[Amit Varma]: in the industry that uses virtual reality to make their customized aluminium products.

00:03:29.880 --> 00:03:33.360
[Amit Varma]: They've had a massive impact that is unseen in two ways.

00:03:33.360 --> 00:03:37.280
[Amit Varma]: One, of course, they make the building they are used for sturdier and more reliable.

00:03:37.280 --> 00:03:42.940
[Amit Varma]: Two, they've brought value to the entire industry, and not just the industry, but also the environment

00:03:42.940 --> 00:03:48.040
[Amit Varma]: as projects that use KNST use less wood and are friendlier to the natural world around

00:03:48.040 --> 00:03:49.040
[Amit Varma]: them.

00:03:49.040 --> 00:03:54.080
[Amit Varma]: This shows that not only is sustainable development possible in these urbanizing times, but also

00:03:54.080 --> 00:03:56.840
[Amit Varma]: that India can show the way in how it's done.

00:03:56.840 --> 00:03:59.720
[Amit Varma]: Their slogan goes, Desh Mein Bana, Desh Ka Apna.

00:03:59.720 --> 00:04:02.760
[Amit Varma]: And companies like this are the Atmanirbhar India I like.

00:04:02.760 --> 00:04:06.640
[Amit Varma]: They're already multinational, by the way, building not just for this country, but for

00:04:06.640 --> 00:04:07.640
[Amit Varma]: the world.

00:04:07.640 --> 00:04:10.960
[Amit Varma]: To know more about KNST, check out knstaluform.com.

00:04:10.960 --> 00:04:13.400
[Amit Varma]: The link will be at the bottom of the show notes.

00:04:13.400 --> 00:04:14.400
[Amit Varma]: KNST.

00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:19.240
[Amit Varma]: Technology, design, innovation, they all come together in KNST.

00:04:19.240 --> 00:04:23.040
[Guest]: Avijit, welcome to the scene and the unseen.

00:04:23.040 --> 00:04:24.920
[Amit Varma]: Thank you so much for having me here.

00:04:24.920 --> 00:04:30.000
[Amit Varma]: You know, I really enjoyed reading your book and watching all your videos and all of that,

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:34.720
[Amit Varma]: because you are doing something so well in that, that I kind of aspire to and try to

00:04:34.720 --> 00:04:40.720
[Amit Varma]: do myself, which is that you look at the world through broad frameworks, you've taken a step

00:04:40.720 --> 00:04:44.360
[Amit Varma]: back, you know, most people, they're just involved in the everyday running of the world

00:04:44.360 --> 00:04:45.560
[Amit Varma]: and all of that.

00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:48.560
[Amit Varma]: And you've taken a step back and you're looking, you're getting meta, you're looking at first

00:04:48.560 --> 00:04:51.800
[Amit Varma]: principles, you're applying them to everything that you see.

00:04:51.800 --> 00:04:55.920
[Amit Varma]: It is not only in your field HR, which you're an expert in, but you can extrapolate any

00:04:55.920 --> 00:05:01.240
[Amit Varma]: of them to a whole bunch of things like while reading your book, I was like, this is a thought

00:05:01.240 --> 00:05:02.680
[Amit Varma]: I have had about that.

00:05:02.680 --> 00:05:04.780
[Amit Varma]: And now I see it in this context.

00:05:04.780 --> 00:05:06.680
[Amit Varma]: And all the dots are kind of joining.

00:05:06.680 --> 00:05:10.440
[Amit Varma]: So I'm really looking forward to our conversation today.

00:05:10.440 --> 00:05:14.880
[Amit Varma]: But the part of it that I'm looking forward to is really not about that, you know, these

00:05:14.880 --> 00:05:20.640
[Amit Varma]: days, I love kind of getting into people's early lives and memories, their childhoods

00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:21.640
[Amit Varma]: and all of that.

00:05:21.640 --> 00:05:27.960
[Amit Varma]: Because I think in this modern world, where we are always stuck in the immediate moment,

00:05:27.960 --> 00:05:34.600
[Amit Varma]: and we take everything, every change for granted, I think we often forget how much our lives

00:05:34.600 --> 00:05:36.560
[Amit Varma]: have changed, like I'm 48.

00:05:36.560 --> 00:05:41.560
[Amit Varma]: And I look back on how I used to live in the 80s and 90s, and all of that, ki abhi toh

00:05:41.560 --> 00:05:43.880
[Amit Varma]: we have all the music in the world available to us.

